(36, 1, '2020-06-21 03:31:47', '2020-06-21 03:31:47', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On this page</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/create-atlas-account/#considerations\">Considerations</a></li><li><a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/create-atlas-account/#register-a-new-service-account\">Register a new Atlas Account</a></li><li><a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/create-atlas-account/#login-to-your-service-account\">Login to Your Atlas Account</a></li><li><a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/create-atlas-account/#next-steps\">Next Steps</a></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Estimated completion time: 5 minutes</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can register for an Atlas account using your Google Account or an email address.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Considerations</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can register with and login using your Google account or using your email account.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Google Accounts</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you register with your Google Account, the following differences apply when using your Google account with Atlas:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Google manages your user details, email address, and password. You can’t change this information using the Atlas console or&nbsp;<abbr title=\"Application Programming Interface\">API</abbr>.</li><li>Google manages your&nbsp;<abbr title=\"Two Factor Authentication\">2FA</abbr>. You can’t use Atlas&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/security-two-factor-authentication/\">two factor authentication</a>&nbsp;and won’t be prompted for an Atlas&nbsp;<abbr title=\"Two Factor Authentication\">2FA</abbr>&nbsp;verification when you log into Atlas. Google should verify your identity using&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.google.com/landing/2step/\">Google 2-Step Verification</a></li><li>Google creates a new Atlas account if you change your Google Account email address. Ask your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/reference/user-roles/#Organization-Owner\"><code>Organization&nbsp;Owner</code></a>&nbsp;or MongoDB Support to link this new account with your existing organizations and projects.</li><li>You can unlink your Google Account from Atlas. Refer to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/3466521?hl=en\">Google Account Help article</a>&nbsp;to unlink your Atlas account from your Google Account.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>MongoDB Cloud Manager Users</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you use MongoDB Cloud Manager, use your Cloud Manager credentials to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/create-atlas-account/#atlas-account-login\">log in</a>&nbsp;to Atlas. You can then create a new Atlas project from Cloud Manager.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Register a new Atlas Account</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Start at the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://account.mongodb.com/account/register\">MongoDB Atlas registration page</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Google Account</li><li>Email Address</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Sign up with Google</strong>.</li><li>Enter one of the following identifiers for your Google account:<ul><li>your Gmail or Google Apps email address</li><li>the phone number associated with your Google account</li></ul></li><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Next</strong>.</li><li>Enter the password for your Google account.</li><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Next</strong>.</li><li>Review and select the checkbox to accept the&nbsp;<strong>Terms of Service</strong>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<strong>Privacy Policy</strong>.</li><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Submit</strong>.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After you register, Atlas creates an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/organizations-projects/\">organization and project</a>&nbsp;where you can deploy your first cluster. You can add more organizations and projects later.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Login to Your Atlas Account</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you already created a MongoDB account using your Google account, sign in to your Google account:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Navigate to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://account.mongodb.com/account/login\">MongoDB Atlas login page</a>.</li><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Login</strong>.</li><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Log in with Google</strong>.</li><li>Follow the prompts to log in using your Google account.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Next Steps</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With your Atlas account, proceed to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/deploy-free-tier-cluster/\">Deploy a Free Tier Cluster</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>© MongoDB, Inc 2008-present. MongoDB, Mongo, and the leaf logo are registered trademarks of MongoDB, Inc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Create an Atlas Account', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'create-an-atlas-account', '', '', '2020-06-21 03:32:00', '2020-06-21 03:32:00', '', 0, 'http://localhost/auteros.document.com/?p=36', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(37, 1, '2020-06-21 03:31:47', '2020-06-21 03:31:47', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On this page</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li><a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/create-atlas-account/#considerations\">Considerations</a></li><li><a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/create-atlas-account/#register-a-new-service-account\">Register a new Atlas Account</a></li><li><a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/create-atlas-account/#login-to-your-service-account\">Login to Your Atlas Account</a></li><li><a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/create-atlas-account/#next-steps\">Next Steps</a></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Estimated completion time: 5 minutes</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can register for an Atlas account using your Google Account or an email address.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Considerations</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can register with and login using your Google account or using your email account.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>Google Accounts</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you register with your Google Account, the following differences apply when using your Google account with Atlas:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Google manages your user details, email address, and password. You can’t change this information using the Atlas console or&nbsp;<abbr title=\"Application Programming Interface\">API</abbr>.</li><li>Google manages your&nbsp;<abbr title=\"Two Factor Authentication\">2FA</abbr>. You can’t use Atlas&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/security-two-factor-authentication/\">two factor authentication</a>&nbsp;and won’t be prompted for an Atlas&nbsp;<abbr title=\"Two Factor Authentication\">2FA</abbr>&nbsp;verification when you log into Atlas. Google should verify your identity using&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.google.com/landing/2step/\">Google 2-Step Verification</a></li><li>Google creates a new Atlas account if you change your Google Account email address. Ask your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/reference/user-roles/#Organization-Owner\"><code>Organization&nbsp;Owner</code></a>&nbsp;or MongoDB Support to link this new account with your existing organizations and projects.</li><li>You can unlink your Google Account from Atlas. Refer to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/3466521?hl=en\">Google Account Help article</a>&nbsp;to unlink your Atlas account from your Google Account.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>MongoDB Cloud Manager Users</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you use MongoDB Cloud Manager, use your Cloud Manager credentials to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/create-atlas-account/#atlas-account-login\">log in</a>&nbsp;to Atlas. You can then create a new Atlas project from Cloud Manager.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Register a new Atlas Account</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Start at the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://account.mongodb.com/account/register\">MongoDB Atlas registration page</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Google Account</li><li>Email Address</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Sign up with Google</strong>.</li><li>Enter one of the following identifiers for your Google account:<ul><li>your Gmail or Google Apps email address</li><li>the phone number associated with your Google account</li></ul></li><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Next</strong>.</li><li>Enter the password for your Google account.</li><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Next</strong>.</li><li>Review and select the checkbox to accept the&nbsp;<strong>Terms of Service</strong>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<strong>Privacy Policy</strong>.</li><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Submit</strong>.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After you register, Atlas creates an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/organizations-projects/\">organization and project</a>&nbsp;where you can deploy your first cluster. You can add more organizations and projects later.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Login to Your Atlas Account</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you already created a MongoDB account using your Google account, sign in to your Google account:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li>Navigate to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://account.mongodb.com/account/login\">MongoDB Atlas login page</a>.</li><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Login</strong>.</li><li>Click&nbsp;<strong>Log in with Google</strong>.</li><li>Follow the prompts to log in using your Google account.</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Next Steps</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With your Atlas account, proceed to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.atlas.mongodb.com/tutorial/deploy-free-tier-cluster/\">Deploy a Free Tier Cluster</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>© MongoDB, Inc 2008-present. MongoDB, Mongo, and the leaf logo are registered trademarks of MongoDB, Inc.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Create an Atlas Account', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '36-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-06-21 03:31:47', '2020-06-21 03:31:47', '', 36, 'http://localhost/auteros.document.com/2020/06/21/36-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
